---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ConceptPageHero from '../../components/concepts/ConceptPageHero.astro';
import ConceptPager from '../../components/concepts/ConceptPager.astro';
import { getConcept } from '../../lib/concepts';

const c = getConcept('frequency');
---

<Layout title={`${c.title} | Identity Engineering`}>
	<main class="min-h-screen">
		<ConceptPageHero
			scene={c.scene}
			tag={`${c.tag} · ${c.layerLabel}`}
			title={c.title}
			lede={c.blurb}
			scrollHint={c.scrollHint}
		/>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-8 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/55">
				<div class="mb-2 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Definition</div>
				<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white md:text-4xl">
					The dynamic state of the tension continuum.
				</h2>
				<p>
					<strong class="text-white/80">Frequency</strong> is the engineering descriptor of the high-dimensional tension continuum in which identities exist and interact. It captures the spectrum of characteristic oscillation frequencies, resonance conditions and damping ratios that determine how an identity’s internal tension field evolves over time.
				</p>
				<p>
					Frequency is scale-aware: the same conceptual language applies both to individual identities and to emergent collective identities, even though the characteristic frequencies and relevant damping mechanisms differ across scales.
				</p>
				<div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-black/30 p-6">
					<div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[3px] text-white/40 mb-3">Interpretation lens</div>
					<p class="text-white/60 leading-relaxed">
						Frequency is less about speed for its own sake, and more about pattern quality:
						what repeats, what amplifies, what decays, and what destabilizes under load.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02] px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
				<div class="mb-6 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Mechanics</div>
				<ul class="space-y-6 text-lg text-white/55">
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Tension field:</strong> The high-dimensional continuum of internal stress and deflection an identity is permanently exposed to.
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Frequency spectrum:</strong> The characteristic rates at which tension oscillates and changes. These frequencies encode responsiveness to internal conflicts and external perturbations.
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Resonance:</strong> Frequency matching between identities or between an identity and idea-clusters, producing mutual amplification and energetically favourable coupling.
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Damping (general):</strong> The rate at which tension oscillations decay. It controls energy dissipation and modal stability. Damping is a general parameter of any tension field. Its specific, higher-order application as regulatory or collective damping is treated in the Collective Identity layer (see Damping).
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-8 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/55">
				<div class="mb-2 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Deepening · The Now</div>
				<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white md:text-4xl">
					The tension field as stress tensor
				</h2>
				<p>
					In the singular point of the Now the high-dimensional tension continuum is experienced as a local stress field. In continuum-mechanics language this is a stress tensor: the set of internal forces that act on every surface element of the identity’s configuration space.
				</p>
				<p>
					We write the effective local tensor as the superposition of three primary components:
				</p>
				<ul class="space-y-4">
					<li class="border-l border-cyan-400/30 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">External component</strong> (σ<sub>ext</sub>): forces arising from the curvature and gravitation of surrounding masses — other identities, structures, events. The identity samples these forces through its frequency bandwidth.
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-cyan-400/30 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Past / trajectory component</strong> (σ<sub>past</sub>): the inertial and phase contribution of the owned history. This is not the raw State Differential alone; it is the differential modulated by the <em class="text-white/70 not-italic">narrative frequency</em> of the trajectory — the coherent, owned interpretation that actually exerts force in the Now.
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-violet-400/30 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Future component</strong> (σ<sub>future</sub>): the oscillatory expression of the Vision Gradient / future force term. In the force-balance formalization of Time this appears as the directed push T<sub>F</sub> · ∇O<sub>τ</sub>. In the Now it is experienced as a vibrating directional tension that biases local decisions toward higher option value.
					</li>
				</ul>
				<p>
					The net local force that results from this tensor is the same object that appears in the Time formalization as the stem force:
				</p>
				<div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-black/40 p-6 font-mono text-sm text-violet-200/90">
					<span class="inline-block whitespace-nowrap">F<sub>stem</sub> = T<sub>F</sub> · ∇O<sub>τ</sub>  −  λ · ∇D<sub>id</sub></span>
				</div>
				<p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-white/45">
					<strong class="text-white/65">In plain words:</strong> the total stem force is the future-opening push minus the identity-protection pullback. Frequency describes the oscillatory and resonant dynamics through which this force balance is actually lived in the Now.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02] px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-8 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/55">
				<div class="mb-2 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Decision</div>
				<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white md:text-4xl">
					Local modulation of the tensor
				</h2>
				<p>
					Decision is the capacity to intervene in σ_total / F_stem at the singular point of the Now. It is not an abstract free will floating above the geometry; it is the Architect-level act of reorienting or re-weighting the components of the tension field so that the resulting Owned Act advances the stem.
				</p>
				<p>
					The primary engineering levers remain those already stated in Time: make the historical trajectory explicit enough for a meaningful identity-deviation term, and sharpen future option value so the vision force is not vague. Frequency supplies the additional instruments of resonance and damping that determine how cleanly those levers transmit into the local tensor.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-8 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/55">
				<div class="mb-2 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Narrative</div>
				<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white md:text-4xl">
					The frequency of the trajectory
				</h2>
				<p>
					The mathematical State Differential (δx = dx/dt) is the observed history. The <strong class="text-white/80">narrative of one’s own story</strong> is the active, owned modulation of that history into a coherent oscillatory component of the tension field. It sets phase and amplitude of σ_past.
				</p>
				<p>
					A coherent, empowering narrative produces constructive interference with the future component and stabilizes the rotation of the stem (lower wobble). A dissonant narrative increases internal friction and reduces the effective bandwidth available for decision. The narrative is therefore not decorative; it is a force-bearing frequency layer of the past that acts in the Now.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/55">
				<p>
					<strong class="text-white/80">Engineering work:</strong> Develop sensitivity to the frequency signature of one’s own tension field and of relevant relational fields. Shape internal damping where possible and respond intelligently to external damping inputs. Use Questions as Probes to measure the relative weight of the three tensor components in the current Now.
				</p>
				<div class="mt-8 rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-black/30 p-6">
					<div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[3px] text-white/40 mb-3">Practical prompts</div>
					<ul class="space-y-3 text-white/60 leading-relaxed">
						<li>Which cycles in my week are constructive resonance, and which are destructive loops?</li>
						<li>Where do I need more damping (over-amplification)?</li>
						<li>Where do I need less damping (suppressed momentum)?</li>
						<li>Which of the three tensor components currently dominates my Now — external, narrative-past, or future force?</li>
						<li>What single Owned Act would most cleanly reorient the local tension field toward higher option value?</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<ConceptPager id="frequency" />
	</main>
</Layout>
